<P ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT SIZE="-1" COLOR="GREEN"><I>Rig Veda</I>, tr. by Ralph T.H. Griffith, [1896], at sacred-texts.com</FONT></P><HR></p>  <h3 align="center" align="center">HYMN LXX. Mitra-Varu&#7751;a.</h3>  
<p>1. EVEN far and wide, O Varu&#7751;a and Mitra, doth your grace extend.<br> May I obtain your kind good-will.<br> 2 From you, benignant Gods, may we gain fully food for sustenance.<br> Such, O ye Rudras, my we be.<br> 3 Guard us, O Rudras. with your guar4 save us, ye skilled to save, my we<br> Subdue the Dasyus, we ourselves,<br> 4 Or ne&#146;er may we, O Wondrous Strong, enjoy another's solemn feast,<br> Ourselves, our sons, or progeny.</p>  
